         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden ¶ 4/1/67 ¶ Sir ¶ In reply to your letter of yesterday ¶ J. Moore to M, 3 January 1867. ¶ I have the honor to inform you ¶ , ¶ that no water is used from the Yan Yean works in t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.01.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Moore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Q67/226,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>unit 249, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne botan. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/1/67</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter of yesterday</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Moore to M, 3 January 1867.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to inform you</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that no water is used from the Yan Yean works in the botanic Garden except at night hours or on rainy days. The water made use of during day hours is obtained from the Yarra, the Lake or the rainwater cisterns of the houses. If it exceptionally happens that visitors not properly close the drinking taps it is almost certain that the Gardener in charge of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">respective</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>portion of the Garden or reserves will find the neglect out without much loss of time. To save the plants from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">exsi</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">c</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">cation</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and yet to avoid withdrawal of water from the neighbouring population it has been arranged last year as well as this year, that irrigation is only applied once a week to each portion of the ground &amp; then in very indeed the most moderate quantity &amp; this from 11 p.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m. til 5. a.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m. Even the water carts are at work during these night hours.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be, Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Undersecretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I omitted to mention, that the small reservoirs sunk on the highest points of my groun</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">d are filled o</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n rainy nights &amp; that by gravitation this water (so stored up) is distributed over the lower grounds in open channels during hot days especially on localities where night watering is not readily to be controlled.</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
